\end

In the five-state symmetric Potts model, we previously introduced~\cite{bmv1}
an infinite set of birational transformations of the parameter space.
We deformed in this publication these transformations with two parameters.
A one-parameter family of deformations
preserve the foliation of the parameter space into invariant elliptic curves.
This deformation parameter can be seen heuristically as the number of
colours of a $q$-state chiral Potts model.



